<w:document xmlns:wpc="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingCanvas" xmlns:mo="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/mac/office/2008/main" xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" xmlns:mv="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:mac:vml" xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" xmlns:r="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/officeDocument/2006/relationships" xmlns:m="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/officeDocument/2006/math" xmlns:v="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml" xmlns:wp14="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingDrawing" xmlns:wp="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/wordprocessingDrawing" xmlns:w10="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word" xmlns:w="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/wordprocessingml/2006/main" xmlns:w14="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordml" xmlns:wpg="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingGroup" xmlns:wpi="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingInk" xmlns:wne="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2006/wordml" xmlns:wps="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingShape" mc:Ignorable="w14 wp14"><w:body><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading1"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>GHANA PRISONS INMATES LEARNING PORTAL</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>System Development Workflow &amp; Technical Guide for Codex Implementation</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Deployment Mode: Local Server (Offline Secure Environment)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>1. System Overview</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>The Ghana Prisons Inmates Learning Portal is a secure offline Learning Management System (LMS) designed to run on a local server within prison facilities. The system integrates biometric lab access, inmate learning portal, administrative dashboard, lecturer dashboard, management analytics dashboard, and device allocation tracking.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>The entire solution operates without internet connectivity and ensures high-level security, attendance monitoring, and educational performance tracking.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>2. High-Level System Workflow</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>1. Inmate arrives at lab/hall entrance.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>2. Inmate verifies identity using fingerprint or facial recognition on Clock-In System.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>3. Clocking Officer confirms hall/room and allocates device (Tablet/Laptop/Desktop).</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>4. Device Serial ID is recorded and linked to inmate session.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>5. Inmate is granted lab access.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>6. Inmate opens the Ghana Prisons Inmates Learning Portal on assigned device.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>7. Homepage displays course categories, top courses, and education slider.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>8. Inmate clicks Login button in header and enters credentials.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>9. Inmate continues learning, assignments, and assessments.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>10. Attendance and device usage are logged in the LMS database.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>11. Clocking Officer performs clock-out when inmate leaves (no biometric required).</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>3. Clock-In &amp; Lab Access System</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>The Clock-In system verifies identity, assigns device, tracks hall location, and logs attendance.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:drawing><wp:inline xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:pic="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><wp:extent cx="5486400" cy="3657600"/><wp:docPr id="1" name="Picture 1"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic><a:graphicData uri="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:pic><pic:nvPicPr><pic:cNvPr id="0" name="a_clean_professional_ui_screenshot_illustration_o.png"/><pic:cNvPicPr/></pic:nvPicPr><pic:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId9"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></pic:blipFill><pic:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="5486400" cy="3657600"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"/></pic:spPr></pic:pic></a:graphicData></a:graphic></wp:inline></w:drawing></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Figure 1: Clock-In &amp; Lab Access Interface</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Core Functional Requirements:</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Biometric Verification (Fingerprint / Facial Recognition)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Hall/Room Selection Dropdown</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Device Allocation (Tablet, Laptop, Desktop)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Device Serial ID Entry or Barcode Scan</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Auto-fetch Inmate ID after biometric verification</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Session Time Logging</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Clock-Out Function (Restricted to Clocking Officer)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Attendance Sync to LMS Database</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>4. Inmate Learning Portal</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>The inmate portal runs on assigned devices and allows secure login and course interaction.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:drawing><wp:inline xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:pic="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><wp:extent cx="5486400" cy="3657600"/><wp:docPr id="2" name="Picture 2"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic><a:graphicData uri="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:pic><pic:nvPicPr><pic:cNvPr id="0" name="a_screenshot_of_a_digital_learning_portal_homepage.png"/><pic:cNvPicPr/></pic:nvPicPr><pic:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId10"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></pic:blipFill><pic:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="5486400" cy="3657600"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"/></pic:spPr></pic:pic></a:graphicData></a:graphic></wp:inline></w:drawing></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Figure 2: Inmate Portal Homepage</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Functional Components:</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Homepage with Education Slider</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Course Categories Display</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Top Courses Section</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Header Login Button</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Secure Authentication (Credentials issued by Admin)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Resume Learning</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Track Progress</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Offline Data Synchronization with Local Server</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>5. Administrator Dashboard</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Administrators manage users, courses, permissions, and generate reports.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:drawing><wp:inline xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:pic="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><wp:extent cx="5486400" cy="3657600"/><wp:docPr id="6" name="Picture 6"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic><a:graphicData uri="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:pic><pic:nvPicPr><pic:cNvPr id="0" name="a_screenshot_of_the_ghana_prisons_learning_portal.png"/><pic:cNvPicPr/></pic:nvPicPr><pic:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId13"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></pic:blipFill><pic:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="5486400" cy="3657600"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"/></pic:spPr></pic:pic></a:graphicData></a:graphic></wp:inline></w:drawing></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Figure 3: Administrator Dashboard</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Create/Edit/Delete Inmate Accounts</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Create/Edit/Delete Lecturer Accounts</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Create/Edit/Delete Clocking Officer Accounts</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Assign Roles (Admin / Management Privileges)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Create/Delete Courses</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Upload Course Materials</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- View Attendance Logs</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Generate Reports &amp; Charts</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- AI Predictive Analysis Module</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Data Export (PDF/Excel)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>6. Management Dashboard</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Management dashboard provides analytical oversight of inmate education, attendance, course performance, and predictive insights.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:drawing><wp:inline xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:pic="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><wp:extent cx="5486400" cy="3657600"/><wp:docPr id="4" name="Picture 4"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic><a:graphicData uri="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:pic><pic:nvPicPr><pic:cNvPr id="0" name="a_dashboard_for_the_ghana_prisons_learning_portal.png"/><pic:cNvPicPr/></pic:nvPicPr><pic:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId11"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></pic:blipFill><pic:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="5486400" cy="3657600"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"/></pic:spPr></pic:pic></a:graphicData></a:graphic></wp:inline></w:drawing></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Figure 4: Management Analytics Dashboard</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- View Registration Statistics</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Attendance Analytics</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Course Performance Metrics</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Lecturer Performance Reports</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- AI-Based Future Predictions (Enrollment &amp; Performance Trends)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Downloadable Executive Reports</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>7. Lecturer Dashboard</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:drawing><wp:inline xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:pic="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><wp:extent cx="5486400" cy="3657600"/><wp:docPr id="5" name="Picture 5"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic><a:graphicData uri="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:pic><pic:nvPicPr><pic:cNvPr id="0" name="a_screenshot_of_a_teacher_s_account_in_the_ghana_p.png"/><pic:cNvPicPr/></pic:nvPicPr><pic:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId12"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></pic:blipFill><pic:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="5486400" cy="3657600"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"/></pic:spPr></pic:pic></a:graphicData></a:graphic></wp:inline></w:drawing></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Figure 5: Lecturer Dashboard</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Functional Capabilities:</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Upload Course Content (PDF, Video, Notes)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Monitor Student Attendance</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Monitor Student Performance</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Create Assignments &amp; Tests</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Allocate Marks</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Manual Grading Option</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Auto-Grading Option (Answer Key Submission)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- View Analytics per Course</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>8. Unified Access Entry Page</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:drawing><wp:inline xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:pic="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><wp:extent cx="5486400" cy="3657600"/><wp:docPr id="7" name="Picture 7"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic><a:graphicData uri="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:pic><pic:nvPicPr><pic:cNvPr id="0" name="a_digital_screenshot_displays_the_unified_access_e.png"/><pic:cNvPicPr/></pic:nvPicPr><pic:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId14"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></pic:blipFill><pic:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="5486400" cy="3657600"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"/></pic:spPr></pic:pic></a:graphicData></a:graphic></wp:inline></w:drawing></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>The system entry link displays five buttons for role-based access:</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>1. Admin Login</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>2. Management Login</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>3. Lecturer Login</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>4. Inmate Login</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>5. Lab Access &amp; Clock-In</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>9. Technical Architecture Guidance for Codex</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Recommended Stack (Offline Environment):</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Backend: Laravel / Node.js (Local Server Deployment)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Database: MySQL (Hosted Locally)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Biometric Integration API (Local SDK)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- RESTful API Architecture</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Local Network Deployment (Intranet)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Device Logging Module</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>- Audit Trail &amp; Activity Logs</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>All modules must communicate through secure API endpoints within the local server. Biometric logs and attendance records must synchronize with LMS user session data.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>10. Full System Architecture Diagram</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>This architecture diagram shows how all user-facing interfaces communicate with the same offline local server. It also maps the major application services and the shared data storage layer that supports security, attendance, learning, and reporting.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:drawing><wp:inline xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:pic="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><wp:extent cx="5852160" cy="3669211"/><wp:docPr id="8" name="Picture 8"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic><a:graphicData uri="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:pic><pic:nvPicPr><pic:cNvPr id="0" name="system_architecture.png"/><pic:cNvPicPr/></pic:nvPicPr><pic:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId15"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></pic:blipFill><pic:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="5852160" cy="3669211"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"/></pic:spPr></pic:pic></a:graphicData></a:graphic></wp:inline></w:drawing></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:jc w:val="center"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:rPr><w:i/><w:sz w:val="20"/></w:rPr><w:t>Figure 6: Full System Architecture Diagram</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>11. Database ERD</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>The ERD defines the core entities required for implementation. It links user accounts, inmate and staff profiles, courses, enrollments, attendance logs, clock-in sessions, rooms, devices, assignments, and submissions.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:drawing><wp:inline xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:pic="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><wp:extent cx="5852160" cy="3862789"/><wp:docPr id="9" name="Picture 9"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic><a:graphicData uri="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:pic><pic:nvPicPr><pic:cNvPr id="0" name="database_erd.png"/><pic:cNvPicPr/></pic:nvPicPr><pic:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId16"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></pic:blipFill><pic:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="5852160" cy="3862789"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"/></pic:spPr></pic:pic></a:graphicData></a:graphic></wp:inline></w:drawing></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:jc w:val="center"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:rPr><w:i/><w:sz w:val="20"/></w:rPr><w:t>Figure 7: Database Entity Relationship Diagram</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>12. UML Use Case Diagram</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>The use case diagram identifies the major system actors and the primary actions each actor performs within the Ghana Prisons Inmates Learning Portal.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:drawing><wp:inline xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:pic="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><wp:extent cx="5852160" cy="3669211"/><wp:docPr id="10" name="Picture 10"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic><a:graphicData uri="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:pic><pic:nvPicPr><pic:cNvPr id="0" name="uml_use_case.png"/><pic:cNvPicPr/></pic:nvPicPr><pic:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId17"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></pic:blipFill><pic:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="5852160" cy="3669211"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"/></pic:spPr></pic:pic></a:graphicData></a:graphic></wp:inline></w:drawing></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:jc w:val="center"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:rPr><w:i/><w:sz w:val="20"/></w:rPr><w:t>Figure 8: UML Use Case Diagram</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>13. UML Sequence Diagram</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>This sequence diagram models the interaction flow from inmate biometric check-in through access validation, device allocation, and loading the inmate learning portal.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:drawing><wp:inline xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:pic="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><wp:extent cx="5852160" cy="3843945"/><wp:docPr id="11" name="Picture 11"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic><a:graphicData uri="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:pic><pic:nvPicPr><pic:cNvPr id="0" name="uml_sequence.png"/><pic:cNvPicPr/></pic:nvPicPr><pic:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId18"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></pic:blipFill><pic:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="5852160" cy="3843945"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"/></pic:spPr></pic:pic></a:graphicData></a:graphic></wp:inline></w:drawing></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:jc w:val="center"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:rPr><w:i/><w:sz w:val="20"/></w:rPr><w:t>Figure 9: UML Sequence Diagram</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>14. UML Activity Diagram</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>The activity diagram summarizes the end-to-end operational flow from arrival at the lab entrance to learning session logging and clock-out control.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:drawing><wp:inline xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:pic="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><wp:extent cx="5303520" cy="6987620"/><wp:docPr id="12" name="Picture 12"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic><a:graphicData uri="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/picture"><pic:pic><pic:nvPicPr><pic:cNvPr id="0" name="uml_activity.png"/><pic:cNvPicPr/></pic:nvPicPr><pic:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId19"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></pic:blipFill><pic:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="5303520" cy="6987620"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"/></pic:spPr></pic:pic></a:graphicData></a:graphic></wp:inline></w:drawing></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:jc w:val="center"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:rPr><w:i/><w:sz w:val="20"/></w:rPr><w:t>Figure 10: UML Activity Diagram</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:sectPr w:rsidR="00FC693F" w:rsidRPr="0006063C" w:rsidSect="00034616"><w:pgSz w:w="12240" w:h="15840"/><w:pgMar w:top="1440" w:right="1800" w:bottom="1440" w:left="1800" w:header="720" w:footer="720" w:gutter="0"/><w:cols w:space="720"/><w:docGrid w:linePitch="360"/></w:sectPr></w:body></w:document>